This paper is concerned with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for paraphrase detection, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper proposes a novel deep neural network-based approach for detecting paraphrases in short text messages, which is a common problem in social media and other user-generated content. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
